1)  Install latest java jdk from oracle website
      To check: Open terminal --> java - version

2) Install intellij community edition 

3) Set java home path in terminal
      a) Open terminal(Below in LHS are commands)
      b) echo $JAVA_HOME         --> if it returns blank, means path is not set
      c) /usr/libexec/java_home  --> copy the path returned by this command
      d) pwd                     --> check if .zshenv file is present in your system, if not create it in next step
      e) touch ~/.zshenv         --> to create .zshenv file
      f) open ~/.zshenv         --> to open .zshenv file
      g) PASTE the copied path in above steps into this file. ie write this --> Export JAVA_HOME=CopiedPath
      h) cat ~/.zshenv

      i) echo $JAVA_HOME  --> Check if JAVA path is properly set


      

      
